  <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#hasConstraint"/>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/myontology#hasSubConstraint">
  <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Enables the nesting of constraints within a parent constraint to form complex logical expressions.</rdfs:comment>
  <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has sub constraint</rdfs:label>
  <vaem:rationale>[Pitfall Resolution Agent] Added owl:inverseOf axiom pointing to isSubConstraintOf: OOPS pitfall: Relationship does not have an inverse relationship defined within the ontology.</vaem:rationale>
  <dc:source>(competency_question) CQ13: Shall ODRLv2 allow for nested constraints?
    (pitfall) This pitfall appears when any relationship does not have an inverse relationship (owl:inverseOf) defined within the ontology.</dc:source>
